| Name = Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami | Generation = {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 15th generation | Predecessor = {{ill|Ame-no-Hibaraooshinadomi-no-Kami|ja|天日腹大科度美神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Successor = None | Divine Order = {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Full Name = 遠津山岬多良斯神 (Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami) | Alternate Name= 遠津山岬帯神 | Divine Rank = | Divine Role = Agricultural deity | Mausoleum = | father = Ame-no-Hibaraooshinadomi-no-Kami | mother = {{ill|Totsumachine no Kami|ja|遠津待根神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Relatives = | consort = None recorded | children = None recorded | cult_centre = {{Plainlist| * Narumi-no-Ki Shrine * Yamamisaki Shrine }} | Texts = {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft}} }}
'''Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami''' (遠津山岬多良斯神, トオツヤマサキタラシ) is a deity mentioned in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He is the last of the 17 spirits of the world. <ref>新潮日本古典集成 古事記</ref>。
== Overview == Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami appears exclusively in the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' and is the final deity in the {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} lineage. He is described as the 14th descendant of the first deity in this lineage, {{ill|Yashimajinumi|lt=Yashimajinumi no Kami|ja|八島士奴美神|1=Yashimajinumi|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. His name is also recorded as '''Totsuyamasakiobi no Kami''' (遠津山岬帯神).
The name "Totsuyamasakitarashi" can be interpreted as: - "Totsu" (遠津): "Far-off" or "distant," inherited from his mother, Totsumachine no Kami. - "Yamasaki" (山岬): Refers to "mountain promontory," often associated with elevated fertile lands enriched by mountain waters. - "Tarashi" (多良斯): Implies "plenitude" or "sufficiency," symbolizing abundance and agricultural prosperity.{{Sfn|Nishimiya|2014|p=384}}
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (from the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red represents female deities, and yellow represents deities of unknown gender.]] Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami is the son of {{ill|Ame-no-Hibaraooshinadomi-no-Kami|ja|天日腹大科度美神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, himself a descendant of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and Totsumachine no Kami, a daughter of {{ill|Amanosagiri no Kami|ja|天之狭霧神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
He is the last deity recorded in the ''Kojiki'' under the lineage of the {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, with no further genealogical information provided.
== Shrines Dedicated == * '''Narumi-no-Ki Shrine''' ({{ill|Inuyama|ja|犬山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) ** Principal deity. * '''Yamamisaki Shrine''' ({{ill|Unnan|ja|雲南市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shimane Prefecture|ja|島根県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) ** Located within the grounds of {{ill|Nihara Shrine|ja|日原神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} as an auxiliary shrine. * '''Kōtari Shrine''' ({{ill|Nagaokakyō|ja|長岡京市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) ** Currently enshrines {{ill|Amatsu Hikone|ja|天神足命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, though {{ill|Motoori Norinaga|ja|本居宣長|qq=draft|qq=draft}} identified the original deity as Totsuyamasakitarashi no Kami.
